A. D. REYNOLDS, Jr., and Grace Reynolds, v. Seldon R. GLENN, Collector of Internal Revenue for the District of Kentucky. No. 7161. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Oct. 7, 1936. Woodward, Dawson & Hobson and Edward P. Humphrey, all of Louisville, Ky., for appellant. Bunk Gardner, U. S. Atty., of Louisville, Ky., for appellee.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the appeal herein be and the same is dismissed pursuant to motion of appellants.
